Maho (2009) lists the C141 Enyele (Inyele), C142 Bondongo, and C142 Mbonzo (Impfondo)<ref>Not the same as nearby [[Bonjo language|Bonjo]], which has the same name.</ref> languages, which do not have ISO codes, as being closest to Bomitaba.<ref name="Guthrie"/>
