{{Infobox diocese |jurisdiction = Diocese |name = Mahagi–Nioka |latin = Dioecesis Mahagiensis-Niokaensis |country = Democratic Republic of the Congo |metropolitan = [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Kisangani|Kisangani]] |rite = [[Latin Rite]] |cathedral = |cocathedral = |area_km2 = 18,490 |population = 1,563,633 |population_as_of = 2004 |catholics = 858,789 |catholics_percent= 54.9 |pope = {{Incumbent pope}} |bishop = [[Sosthène Ayikuli Udjuwa]] |coadjutor = |auxiliary_bishops= }}
The '''Roman Catholic Diocese of Mahagi–Nioka''' ({{lang-la|Mahagien(sis) – Niokaën(sis)}}) is a [[diocese]] located in the city of [[Mahagi]]–[[Nioka]] in the [[Ecclesiastical province]] of [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Kisangani|Kisangani]] in the [[Democratic Republic of the Congo]].
==History== * July 2, 1962: Established as Diocese of Mahagi from the [[Diocese of Bunia]] * October 30, 1967: Renamed as Diocese of Mahagi – Nioka
==Leadership== * [[Bishop]]s of Mahagi–Nioka ([[Latin Rite]]) ** Bishop Sosthène Ayikuli Udjuwa (2010.11.16 - present) ** Bishop Marcel Utembi Tapa (2001.10.16 – 2008.11.28) ** Bishop [[Alphonse-Marie Runiga Musanganya]] (1980.09.04 – 2001.10.16) ** Bishop [[Thomas Kuba Thowa]] (1967.10.30 – 1979.10.10) * Bishops of Mahagi (Latin Rite) ** Bishop Thomas Kuba Thowa (1962.07.02 – 1967.10.30)
==See also== *[[Roman Catholicism in the Democratic Republic of the Congo]]
==Sources== * [http://www.gcatholic.org/dioceses/diocese/maha0.htm GCatholic.org] * [http://www.catholic-hierarchy.org/diocese/dmaha.html Catholic Hierarchy]
